    "comment": "Rationale: 9/11/2017 Pim\n\nFig. 7: BAI1 interacts with cell polarity machinery.\nFig.9: Loss of BAI1 alters Rac1 activation and F-actin in hippocampal neurons.\nFig.10: BAI1 interaction with Par3/Tiam1 is required for spinogenesis and Par3 localization.\nFi.g11: BAI1 signals to Rac1 through Tiam1.. Experimental description: Experiments were done in mouse and rats\nLiteral \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from E19 Long-Evans rats as described previously.\n\"In utero electroporation was performed as described previously (Hedstrom et al.,2007). We introduced shRNA or vector plasmids\ntogether with pCx-EGFP (CAG promoterdriving EGFP expression) into ICR mice\n(Charles River) at E14.\n\n9/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed BAI1 protein is of human species; \"Human BAI1 was obtained from Y. Nakamura (University of Tokyo) \". Since endogenous rat protein was also visualized annotation is made against rat species.",
